tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  16,112,"Such superficial people of Noah’s community made fun of him but, in reality, they were themselves about to become the subject of ridicule."
  16,117,"The system of ‘cause and effect’ in this world is only a veil otherwise, whatever is happening happens by the direct orders of God. It is the test of a human being that he should be able to tear asunder the outward veil and see the reality he should discover the divine powers working behind the screen of cause and effect."